
generate_si_cache 	- User's Manual

DESCRIPTION:
	generate_si_cache is a stand-alone PC utility developed to convert the the given SI Cache file from binary to XML format or vice versa based on the specified mode. This utility helps to enhance the existing channel map to support the development activities at locations where MSO head-end connectivity is not available. This utility uses Libxml2 XML toolkit (http://xmlsoft.org/) for all XML related operations.

PRE-REQUISITES:
	Libxml2 XML toolkit must be installed in the build machine. More details can be obtained from the site (http://xmlsoft.org/). Default location where the utility searches for libxml2 in linux machine is "/usr/include/libxml2". If libxml2 is installed in some other location, change the location of the macros, LIBXML2_INCL and LIBXML2_LIBDIR accordingly in build.sh.
	
BUILD INSTRUCTIONS:
	To generate the utility:

	(i) 'cd' to the utility's root directory and type
		./build.sh
	    This will generate Makefiles, compile source code and create SI Cache Converter binary. The binary will be available in '<utility's root directory>/bin' directory

	(ii) To remove the utility binaries and object files, run the below command:
		 `./build.sh --clean'.

	(iii) To remove all object files, utility binaries, Makefiles and autogenerated configuration files, run the below command
		 `./build.sh --cleanall'.

USAGE: 
	./generate_si_cache [-mode MODE] [-input INPUT_FILE] [-output OUTPUT_FILE] [-sioutput SIOUTPUT_FILE] [-snsoutput SNSOUTPUT_FILE] [-help] [-version]

OPTIONS:
	-mode		: Operation mode. It can be one of the following:
					xtob - Generate SI Cache binaries from the given XML file
					btox - Generate SI Cache XML file from the given binary file
					dump - Dump channel map from the given binary file to console
	-input    	: Input file. It can be an XML file or a binary SI Cache file depending on the operation mode
	-output   	: Output file. It can be a binary SI Cache file or an XML file depending on the operation mode
	-sioutput 	: Binary SI Cache file to be generated. To use this option, the mode should be set to 'xtob'
	-snsoutput	: Binary SNS Cache file to be generated. To use this option, the mode should be set to 'xtob'
	-version	: Prints the tool's version details
	-help		: Prints this user's manual

EXAMPLES:
(i)   Command to generate binary SI cache from given XML file:
	./generate_si_cache -mode xtob -input si.xml -output SICache

(ii)  Command to generate both binary SI cache and binary SNS cache from given XML file:
	./generate_si_cache -mode xtob -input si.xml -sioutput SICache -snsoutput SNSCache 

(iii) Command to generate XML file from binary SI cache:
	./generate_si_cache -mode btox -input SICache -output si.xml

(iv) Command to dump channel map from binary SI cache to console:
	./generate_si_cache -mode dump -input SICache 
